sequenceDiagram
    participant PA as Project Architect
    participant OE as Orchestration Engine
    participant KR as Knowledge Repository
    participant AAR as AI Agent Runtime
    participant TIG as Tool Integration Gateway
    participant EE as Execution Engine
    participant GM as Governance Module

    PA->>OE: Request architecture view generation (e.g., System Context)
    OE->>OE: Workflow Engine creates architecture workflow
    OE->>OE: Task Manager verifies prerequisite views exist
    OE->>AAR: Assign Generate task to Architecture Agent
    AAR->>KR: Read foundational docs + all prerequisite architecture views
    KR-->>AAR: Foundation, Domain, UL, Domain Model, Sys Arch, prior views
    AAR->>TIG: Invoke AI Provider for view and diagram generation
    TIG-->>AAR: Architecture view content and Mermaid diagram
    AAR-->>OE: Draft .md document + .mmd diagram

    OE->>AAR: Assign Review task to Review Agent
    AAR->>KR: Read draft + existing views + UL for consistency review
    KR-->>AAR: Context for consistency check
    AAR->>TIG: Invoke AI Provider for review
    TIG-->>AAR: Review analysis
    AAR-->>OE: Consistency and quality review report

    OE->>AAR: Assign Validate task to Validation Agent
    AAR->>KR: Read task acceptance criteria
    KR-->>AAR: Acceptance criteria (from task definition)
    AAR-->>OE: Validation result

    OE->>EE: Deliver .md + .mmd + review + validation result
    EE->>EE: Artifact Producer assembles both files
    EE->>EE: Validation Engine: completeness, no implementation details, UL consistency
    EE->>GM: Submit for governance

    GM->>GM: Architectural consistency check against existing views
    GM->>PA: Route to Approval Gate
    PA-->>GM: Approval decision

    alt Approved
        GM->>GM: Audit Logger records event
        GM->>KR: Store view in Architecture Repository
        KR-->>OE: New view available for dependent tasks
    else Rejected
        GM->>OE: Rejection report
        OE->>PA: Report delivered
    end
